Team Assistant (Temporary Contract) CharterhouseDubai, UAERef: GP186-1747The RoleThe RoleCharterhouse is working with a global pharmaceutical business based in Dubai with headquarters in Healthcare City. Our client has over 200 employees in the region and due to rapid expansion of the senior management team they are looking to hire a temporary Team Assistant to join their diverse workforce for a period of six months. You will plan extensive travel arrangements, liaising with external agencies and making multi-stop bookings for a team of 20 Executives. You will work alongside one Executive Assistant and another team Secretary, but this role does require candidates to be independent and able to work under pressure. RequirementsRequirementsThe successful candidate should have at least two years experience from an administration or secretarial background and be able to deal with a large workload and strict time constraints.
You should be educated to at least high school standard, have previous UAE work experience and excellent English communication skills. In addition it is essential you are meticulous as there is no room for error with the Executives having such busy diaries and schedules. About the CompanyAbout the CompanyDuring the last ten years, Charterhouse has been operating across Dubai, Abu Dhabi and the GCC Markets. In many ways, we were the recruiter who established and set the standards within the regional recruitment industry benchmarking and innovating the service levels associated to Search and Selection. Charterhouse understands the dynamics attached to talent acquisition, relationship management and the required service levels within the regional industry. Our heritage is now our main strength as we continu (more...)
